%global packname  howmany
%global packver   0.3-1
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.3.1
Release:          3%{?dist}
Summary:          A lower bound for the number of correct rejections

License:          GPL
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-graphics 
BuildRequires:    R-stats 
Requires:         R-graphics 
Requires:         R-stats 

%description
When testing multiple hypotheses simultaneously, this package provides
functionality to calculate a lower bound for the number of correct
rejections (as a function of the number of rejected hypotheses), which
holds simultaneously -with high probability- for all possible number of
rejections.  As a special case, a lower bound for the total number of
false null hypotheses can be inferred.  Dependent test statistics can be
handled for multiple tests of associations. For independent test
statistics, it is sufficient to provide a list of p-values.

